This place really flies under the radar.  My girlfriend and I discovered this this a few years ago, have been many times, and a recent terrible experience at another steakhouse reminded me how a positive review for Eddie V's is very overdo.  The ambiance and general feel of the restaurant is a perfect mix of classy, romantic, but modern.  The Jazz vibes are welcome and whether at the bar or the booth, it's a good experience.  I've had many things here, but what always sticks out to me is that you can get a fantastic steak (both filet and NY strip are excellent) that is good every time and undercuts other big name steakhouses on price. Another big winner, which I believe is only on special once in a while, is the smoked old fashion which uses fresh smoked wood to essence the glass before a table side cocktail is made.  This drink is pricey, but worth every penny.  In 3 years and several visits I don't think we've had a side that wasn't good so you really can't wrong there.  I can't comment on the seafood as it's hard to not take advantage of the great steak, but maybe some day.  This is a go to spot for us and I have recommended it to many others.  Only thing I don't like is that the popularity is catching on over the last year or two it's harder for us to get a last minute reservation now!

I've been here a few times but I'm generally underwhelmed after each visit.  The good parts of my visits here is that the servers have always been on point with their service and doing their best to make sure their tables are taken care of.  This place does get busy so be prepared for a bit of a wait. On this last visit we started with the tuna tartar (which is always fabulous), we then had the lobster bisque and the crispy shrimp (both were solid) but for the main dishes is where it just didn't hit the mark. My dinner guest had the filet mignon and I had the salmon.  So for starters the filet mignon was overcooked it was closer to well done instead of the medium rare that my guest requested, and way to much truffle that overwhelmed the mashed potatoes.  My salmon was cooked beautifully but lacked salt, and the carrots and spinach were just not there.  The carrots were undercooked and just oddly hard and the spinach was mushy and had an almost bitter taste.  We also opted for getting the truffle mac & cheese as a side but again heavyhanded with the truffle and missing some salt. We ended the night with a sorbet and that was a great palate cleanser.  So overall a safe choice if you're in the area but for me I think it might be a while before I visit again.
